<br>
Mercs/BMs:<br>
<br>
Increase Base damage by .5% per spec level just like left axe with no change in style damage.  (effect: helps out BM/Mercs without helping or hurting low spec nightshades and infiltrators)<br>
<br>
Berserkers:<br>
<br>
change frenzy to be 35%-70% crits instead of 1-100 removing the high end 1-2shot kill ability.<br>
<br>
All weapon users:<br>
<br>
Cap weaponskill at 1700; removing the &quot;breaking&quot; of resists by capping on many opponents when weapon skill breaks 1700.<br>
<br>
But hell, that would mean they actually know there own game.<br>
<br>
Do I as a zerk before 1.62 do more damage (no counting frenzy) then BMs and Mercs? Yes I do.  Do I do more then LW Heroes or Polearms?  No I don't.  <br>
Sure, Zerks are swinging slightly faster to hit consistantly near high-spec 2handed but people keep forgetting that to do this, zerks may be benefitting from the &quot;haste&quot; effect but they are also reducing there quickness as much as possible slowing down the swing and removing much of that haste effect.<br>
<br>
A troll zerk with 35 quick swinging a 4.2/2.4 setup (3.3 avg) vs. a Polearm at 6.0 spd and 140 quick.  That polearm is still going to be swinging slower... but the zerk is going to be swinging closer to 4.0spd and the polearm close or under 5.0 spd.  Not as great a disparity as they want you to believe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raeloran@lighttanksofdaoc>Raeloran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#000000>(4/28/03 6:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=105.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New document purporting to show errors in Waterman doc</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>One interesting bit, a lot of Waterman's cals used a 2.2 left hand wep for Left Axe. There are NO 2.2 delay weps in Midgard, crafted, quest, or drop.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If you look in the original Waterman doc, you can find this:<br>
